.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "May 2026" "simple_shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a small command line interpreter that reads commands from standard input and
executes them with
.BR execve (2).

In interactive mode, the shell displays the prompt
.B "$ "
before waiting for input.

This implementation supports command lines containing a command followed by
optional arguments. It does not search the PATH, so commands must be executable
paths such as
.B /bin/ls
or
.B ./program.
.SH EXAMPLES
.B ./simple_shell

.B $ /bin/echo hello
